1% of them comes

00:11:51.980 --> 00:11:53.574
to Wright and
Company, 200 people,

00:11:53.574 --> 00:11:55.490
that's incrementally
going to be a much better

00:11:55.490 --> 00:11:57.290
Wednesday than we
would normally have.

00:11:57.290 --> 00:12:00.480
So five events a week between
the Pistons, the Red Wings,

00:12:00.480 --> 00:12:03.710
and all the concerts, so that
also helps for us, as well.

00:12:03.710 --> 00:12:07.190
So like I said, every
time you read an article,

00:12:07.190 --> 00:12:08.082
you're like, is--

00:12:08.082 --> 00:12:10.040
we seem to be in the
general vicinity of what's

00:12:10.040 --> 00:12:11.300
going on in some
capacity, which is great.

00:12:11.300 --> 00:12:12.841
SPEAKER: Well, and
it does bring down

00:12:12.841 --> 00:12:15.320
a more diverse and unique
crowd than the sports

00:12:15.320 --> 00:12:18.180
crowds that you get at
Ford Field or at the CoPa,

00:12:18.180 --> 00:12:20.090
so that'll be good
for you guys, too.

00:12:20.090 --> 00:12:23.097
And then, us, of course,
when we move down to Detroit.

00:12:23.097 --> 00:12:23.930
We'll all come down.

00:12:23.930 --> 00:12:25.490
MARC DJOZLIJA: And we look
forward to that, as well.

